<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-609-412  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 609 412.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  June 18 1990 v18 n12 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Vendors adapt C++ to low-cost embedded systems development.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Williams, Tom.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Low-cost tools available with Borland International's Turbo C++and Zortech's C++ compiler combined with utilities from Objective:Systems, and Paradigm Systems may bring the cost of a full suiteof 80X86 real-time development software under $1,000.andP;  Objective:Systems offers Interactors C++, an object-oriented real-timeexecutive adapted to Zortech's C++ compiler.andP;  Building inInteractors' calls in place of DOS calls yields real-timefunctionality.andP;  A utility called Zlocate produces Intel Hex andHewlett-Packard absolute outputs from the Zortech compiler output.andO;Paradigm Systems' Locate utility develops ROMable applications forboth Zortech and Borland's compilers.andP;  Paradigm also offers TDREM,a small monitor that allows communication between the BorlandTurbo debugger and the target system.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Borland International Inc. (products)Zortech Inc. (products)Objective Systems (products)Paradigm Systems Co. (products).andO;Product:   Turbo C (Compiler) (computer programs)C (Compiler) (computer programs).andO;Topic:     Software PackagesSystem Development.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>